<div id="review_607110476" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/607110476" />
    <a title="MM" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/3754944-mm"><img alt="MM" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1366338554p2/3754944.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/607110476?book_show_action=true">May 04, 2013</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="MM" class="user" itemprop="url" name="MM" href="/user/show/3754944-mm">MM</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9780892590575" href="/book/show/825445.Islam_Between_East_and_West">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/3754944-mm?shelf=philosophy">philosophy</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/3754944-mm?shelf=islam">islam</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/3754944-mm?shelf=re-read">re-read</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/3754944-mm?shelf=favourites">favourites</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/3754944-mm?shelf=psychology">psychology</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/3754944-mm?shelf=christianity">christianity</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer607110476" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer8791736173000471415">Thought-provoking and insightful, this is a book well worth reading regardless of religious background. Alija Izetbegovic is an erudite and intelligent man whose analysis of reality touches on every aspect of existence: from life to morality to art to law and back again, all focussing on the inherent dualism in humans of spirit and matter. Rather than being a cliche, run-of-the-mill &quot;Islam and Science&quot; book, Izetbegovic thankfully does not once try to find a so-called &quot;scientific miracle&quot; in the</span>
  <span id="freeText8791736173000471415" style="display:none">Thought-provoking and insightful, this is a book well worth reading regardless of religious background. Alija Izetbegovic is an erudite and intelligent man whose analysis of reality touches on every aspect of existence: from life to morality to art to law and back again, all focussing on the inherent dualism in humans of spirit and matter. Rather than being a cliche, run-of-the-mill "Islam and Science" book, Izetbegovic thankfully does not once try to find a so-called "scientific miracle" in the Qur'an, choosing rather to analyse humans based on their experiences. Life is the supreme principle in his thought process, and dualism the result. Upbringing vs drilling, culture vs civilisation, and contemplation vs thought are just some of the topics he addresses. His knowledge of philosophies and politics is amazing, and it was astounding to see the sources (usually secular) he referenced. <br /><br />The second of half of the book, dealing with Islam as the bipolar unity between "pure religion" as represented by Christianity and materialism, is slightly less impressive. While discerning and sophisticated, it seems at times to be preaching to the choir. Nevertheless, this is an important book, and I have no doubt that a second read will be even more enlightening than the first. </span>
  <a data-text-id="8791736173000471415" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

