<div id="review_4285912483" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/4285912483" />
    <a title="Arshak" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/107874814-arshak"><img alt="Arshak" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/u_50x66-632230dc9882b4352d753eedf9396530.png" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/4285912483?book_show_action=true">Nov 19, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Arshak" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Arshak" href="/user/show/107874814-arshak">Arshak</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9780892590575" href="/book/show/825445.Islam_Between_East_and_West">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer4285912483" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer18340315701393233227">Islam between the East and West-Alija Izetbegovic<br/><br/>A modern philosophical book written by an extraordinary mind, Islam between the East and West explores some of the most important questions that have haunted the human mind since the earliest of times.<br/><br/>It examines the innate dualism of human nature, the clash between “culture” and “civilization” with historical examples, and presents Islam as a way that balances both these worldviews. He argues that Islam is not a fully formed solution, but rather </span>
  <span id="freeText18340315701393233227" style="display:none">Islam between the East and West-Alija Izetbegovic<br /><br />A modern philosophical book written by an extraordinary mind, Islam between the East and West explores some of the most important questions that have haunted the human mind since the earliest of times.<br /><br />It examines the innate dualism of human nature, the clash between “culture” and “civilization” with historical examples, and presents Islam as a way that balances both these worldviews. He argues that Islam is not a fully formed solution, but rather a method.<br /><br />Divided into two parts and eight chapters that deal with diverse points of view and beliefs. The atheistic and religious worldview, culture and civilization, creation and evolution, learning and drills, education and meditation, progress and humanism, etc. all are introduced and analyzed. The author presents the view that evolution with all its complexity cannot produce a man, but only a perfect animal. It emphasizes the inherently spiritual nature of human beings and the inability of "civilization" to satisfy man's spiritual needs.<br /><br />Art is also an important point of discussion. Parallels are drawn between Religion and art; the author tries to point out the religious nature of art and culture. Socialism and Communism and other dominant philosophies are scrutinized. The author faults Socialism for reducing man to only its animal nature and needs. The contradiction between ‘humanism’ in culture and ‘progress’ in civilization is examined. The second part of the book looks for a solution to this dilemma and presents Islam as the third way, which balances humanism and progress and satisfies man's spiritual and materialistic needs.<br /><br />Alija Izetbegovic, a lawyer from Sarajevo who would later become the premier President of the newly formed country of Bosnia and Herzegovina was an active member of various human rights and religious rights groups in his youth. The book was originally published in 1980, and it became a cause of the author’s imprisonment due to its “fundamentalist digressions”.<br /><br />The book is an attempt to reconcile Western-Style progress with Islamic values, though some of the fundamental elements of Western Civilization are strongly criticized. This is a kind of a book which has a profound effect on you once you read it, for the better. It can be overwhelming at times; with numerous philosophical references and highly intellectual opinions, but as the author himself mentions in the book, some books have to be read slowly, by understanding every word and pondering on every thought.<br /><br />Islam between the East and West is a rewarding experience for anyone looking for serious reading material. It is a brilliant piece of work; it attempts to dissect the principles on which modern society functions and tries to find a solution to its problems.</span>
  <a data-text-id="18340315701393233227" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

