  <span id="freeText10116036304782007184" style="display:none">When I looked at the price of the book, I thought that the price was exaggerated, but I was mistaken, as when I received the book and read the index, I learned that the book talks about very many topics, each of which that could have been a unique book, meaning that the book contains in its content several books and very abundant topics. In one book, and this corrected my thinking, meaning that I believe that the book is worth every dollar I spent on it.<br />Book content:<br />The book talks about several topics, including the deep-rooted thought in Western and Eastern minds. It also talks about Islam’s position on it and why Islam is distinguished from other beliefs, whether they are spiritualistic or materialistic, and other than that the book also compares and contrasts between these beliefs and gives each of them a logical reason for being reasonable or Wrong, this is only a simple description of the book, meaning that it poses so many other topics.<br />The language of the book is very beautiful, as it is understandable and eloquent at the same time, which makes the book very special and enjoyable to read.<br />Would I recommend this book to others?<br />Answer: I would definitely recommend this book, and this copy that I own will not be the only one that I buy, God willing.</span>
